page.title: 02MATTHEW WILSONS TYPICAL DAY
page.content: I wake up at 7.30a.m. and get out of bed at 7.45a.m.,I then wash and put my uniform on.I go downstairs and say "Morning",to my mum & dad and have breakfast which is cornflakes.Then I search the house for my shoes and start off walking to the bus stop at 8.20a.m.I get there about 8.30a.m.and if it is sunny it comes nearly on time,but if it is raining it comes 25 minutes late.When it does come it takes us to Heversham,drops off some 3rd and 6th formers and then takes the rest of us to Milnthorpe.When I get there I go to my form room and am registered.Then we have school assembly where everybody goes into the hall to be told about any changes happening in the week.When this is finished we go to English for one lesson before moving on to P.E.
